President Obama sent warm wishes on behalf of the American people to India on the occasion of Republic Day. He highlighted the strong shared belief in values such as liberty, pluralism, and religious tolerance between the United States and India. This Republic Day was special as it marked India's Diamond Jubilee, 60 years since the adoption of the Indian Constitution. The President mentioned the strong and vibrant partnership between the two nations and celebrated the friendship between the peoples. He also acknowledged the significant contributions of Indian Americans in various fields in the United States. President Obama called for both governments to continue working together to promote peace, prosperity, and stability globally.